```python -- title="docs_example.cdrm"
Docs??
```

The above command, on a line all by itself will bring up a list of further, similar commands explaining the complete functionality of Fluster and the syntax of Conundrum, the superset of Markdown that powers Fluster.

<Hint>
Consider setting the save method to 'on-save' if the 'on-change' method is too jittery or distracting. Your content is still saved with every keystroke, it just doesn't re-rendered until you press cmd+s.
</Hint>

